title: Russia-Ukraine war: List of key events, day 1,453
partialText: These are the key developments from day 1,453 of Russia’s war on Ukraine.

title: Israel bombs Lebanon-Syria border, kills four people
partialText: Lebanese authorities say Israeli forces bombed a vehicle near the border, killing at least four people.

title: Can the UN Security Council be reformed?
partialText: The UN secretary-general says the absence of African seats is 'indefensible'.

title: Israel kills 11 in Gaza as Trump announces $5bn pledge from Board of Peace
partialText: US President Donald Trump says the first meeting of his newly created Board of Peace will take place on Thursday.

title: Gaza mother’s grim ordeal: A search for missing son among mutilated bodies
partialText: Gaza families seek closure as they search for loved ones among bodies returned by Israel under 'ceasefire' deal.

title: Is Trumpism losing steam?
partialText: As Trumpism forces both major US parties to wonder what they stand for, experts weigh in on November election prospects.

title: Ukraine’s ex-energy minister arrested while trying to cross border
partialText: German Galushchenko was detained by Ukraine's anti-corruption bureau while trying to leave the country.

title: India rout bitter rivals Pakistan at T20 World Cup
partialText: India's win against Pakistan takes the defending champions through to the next round of cricket's T20 World Cup.

title: Syrian army takes over al-Shaddadi base after US withdrawal
partialText: The move, in coordination with the US, is the latest implementation of the ceasefire agreement with Kurdish-led forces.

title: India hammer Pakistan to qualify for T20 World Cup Super Eights
partialText: Ishan Kishan defies a tricky Colombo pitch with 77 as India beat Pakistan by 61 runs in Group A of the T20 World Cup.

title: US ‘not disputing’ European assessment of Navalny poisoning, Rubio says
partialText: Secretary of state says Washington will 'not fight' European partners on their findings as UK considers new sanctions.

title: Thousands of Western nationals fought Israel’s war on Gaza: What to know
partialText: Thousands of Western citizens joined the Israeli military in its war on Gaza that killed over 72,000 Palestinians.

title: As Sudanese city returns to life after two-year siege, drone threat lingers
partialText: Markets reopen in Dilling, South Kordofan’s second largest city. Yet residents face persistent aerial attacks.

title: Iran seeks to get out of FATF blacklist amid domestic political divisions
partialText: North Korea and Myanmar are other two countries on global financial blacklist as Tehran promises countermeasures.

title: Iran’s Araghchi slams European powers for ‘irrelevance’ in nuclear talks
partialText: Foreign minister says regional powers have been 'far more effective' than European countries.

title: Hasan Piker on influence and journalism in the algorithm age
partialText: The political streamer discusses bias, bans, wealth, activism and the blurred line between journalism and influencers.

title: Filmmaker explains why he backs Francesca Albanese amid pressure to resign
partialText: Over 100 artists have signed a letter in support of Francesca Albanese who faces calls to step down as UN rapporteur.

title: Cricket fans ready for hotly-anticipated India-Pakistan T20 World Cup clash
partialText: Supporters of India and Pakistan have flocked to see the highly-anticipated cricket match between archrivals at the ICC.

title: Gaza author and analyst Jehad Abusalim on Trump’s ‘Board of Peace’
partialText: Gaza author Jehad Abusalim speaks to Marc Lamont Hill on Trump’s Board of Peace and the enclave's future.

title: Europeans say Russia poisoned dissident Alexey Navalny with dart frog toxin
partialText: Five European countries say lab tests conclude that Russian opposition leader Alexey Navalny was killed in 2024.

title: Israel approves proposal to register West Bank lands as ‘state property’
partialText: Proposal submitted by far-right Finance Minister Bezalel Smotrich and others, public broadcaster Kan reports.

title: Gaza’s Nasser Hospital slams MSF’s ‘unsubstantiated’ armed men allegation
partialText: Hospital says MSF issued statements that 'misrepresent facts, mirror narratives historically used to justify' attacks.

title: Trump and Netanyahu align on Iran pressure but split on endgame
partialText: Trump, Netanyahu agree to sanction Iranian oil; analysts say Israel is pushing for war to cover West Bank annexation.

title: How the Epstein files exposed victims but protected the powerful
partialText: The release of the Epstein files was supposed to expose a sex trafficking ring. Instead, they exposed the victims.

title: From the Balkans with Guns
partialText: Weapons from the Balkans are fuelling violence on the streets of Sweden. People & Power follows their trail.
